body: This is the second attempt at making toxav stateless. Pretty much just a cherry-pick of the last attempt with a few addition lines. I need someone to tell me how I can duplicate the errors of yesteryear, otherwise I've re-read the whole section of code. Looked at all (or nearly all callbacks) and... well, I works for me! I didn't assign a mile stone yet, as this will replace v..* with v0.1 @iphydf make bug how? @mannol you're awesome, thanks' for toxAV and you keep being you! --- This change is [](https://reviewable.io/reviews/toktok/c-toxcore/282)

*[toxcore/net_crypto.c, line 1442 at r3](https://reviewable.io:443/reviews/toktok/c-toxcore/282#-KYvhNKjKGNwU4jIiqAg:-KYvhNKjKGNwU4jIiqAh:bvxigf1) ([raw file](https://github.com/toktok/c-toxcore/blob/f517fae4ac61ab0a52709c751dfc6d1316b9988d/toxcore/net_crypto.c#L1442)):*
> ```C
>         /* Packet counter. */
>         ++conn->packet_counter;
>     } else if (real_data[0] >= PACKET_ID_LOSSY_RANGE_START && real_data[0] <= PACKET_ID_LOSSY_RANGE_LAST) {
> ```

Again, this should be `real_data[0] >= PACKET_ID_LOSSY_RANGE_START && real_data[0] < PACKET_ID_LOSSY_RANGE_LAST` instead, `<` vs `<=`. `PACKET_ID_LOSSY_RANGE_LAST` equals to `(PACKET_ID_LOSSY_RANGE_START + PACKET_ID_LOSSY_RANGE_SIZE)`, they are both 255, so the comparison should be kept as in the original.

---

*[toxcore/net_crypto.c, line 2639 at r3](https://reviewable.io:443/reviews/toktok/c-toxcore/282#-KYvfPSxVEjlh_b6ftcw:-KYvfPSxVEjlh_b6ftcx:bpnidjo) ([raw file](https://github.com/toktok/c-toxcore/blob/f517fae4ac61ab0a52709c751dfc6d1316b9988d/toxcore/net_crypto.c#L2639)):*
> ```C
>     }
> 
>     if (data[0] < PACKET_ID_LOSSY_RANGE_START || data[0] > PACKET_ID_LOSSY_RANGE_LAST) {
> ```

This should be `data[0] < PACKET_ID_LOSSY_RANGE_START || data[0] >= PACKET_ID_LOSSY_RANGE_LAST` instead, `>=` vs `>`. The original code had `>= PACKET_ID_LOSSY_RANGE_START + PACKET_ID_LOSSY_RANGE_SIZE`, which is `>= 255`.`PACKET_ID_LOSSY_RANGE_LAST` is 255 too, it's the first invalid id after the lossy id block (the last valid lossy id is 254, which would be `PACKET_ID_LOSSY_RANGE_LAST -1`), so since they are the same value, you need to keep the same comparison operator as in the original code.

---

*[toxcore/net_crypto.c, line 2648 at r3](https://reviewable.io:443/reviews/toktok/c-toxcore/282#-KYvfEao-JZYsfY4Oz_d:-KYvfEao-JZYsfY4Oz_e:bcdia9q) ([raw file](https://github.com/toktok/c-toxcore/blob/d8ae726d0a332c74da7bbed70982367dd01899e1/toxcore/net_crypto.c#L2648)):*
> ```C
>     }
> 
>     if (data[0] >= (PACKET_ID_LOSSY_RANGE_START + PACKET_ID_LOSSY_RANGE_SIZE)) {
> ```

See, the does the original code returns `-1` on `data[0] => PACKET_ID_LOSSY_RANGE_LAST` (what was `data[0] >= (PACKET_ID_LOSSY_RANGE_START + PACKET_ID_LOSSY_RANGE_SIZE)`)? Is the last id not inclusive, i.e. `PACKET_ID_LOSSY_RANGE_LAST` should really be 254 instead if we assume the START and LAST as inclusive?

*[toxcore/net_crypto.h, line 79 at r3](https://reviewable.io:443/reviews/toktok/c-toxcore/282#-KYvefongA5-znuTPBTu:-KYvefongA5-znuTPBTv:b-kvu257) ([raw file](https://github.com/toktok/c-toxcore/blob/f517fae4ac61ab0a52709c751dfc6d1316b9988d/toxcore/net_crypto.h#L79)):*
> ```objc
> /* All packets starting with a byte in this range are considered lossless packets. */
> #define PACKET_ID_LOSSLESS_RANGE_START  160
> #define PACKET_ID_LOSSLESS_RANGE_LAST   191
> ```

`START` and `LAST`? Why not `START` and `END` or `FIRST` and `LAST`?

---

*[toxcore/net_crypto.h, line 82 at r3](https://reviewable.io:443/reviews/toktok/c-toxcore/282#-KYvejICq3jVhqO7zfOU:-KYvejICq3jVhqO7zfOV:b11ir3j) ([raw file](https://github.com/toktok/c-toxcore/blob/f517fae4ac61ab0a52709c751dfc6d1316b9988d/toxcore/net_crypto.h#L82)):*
> ```objc
> /* All packets starting with a byte in this range are considered lossy packets. */
> #define PACKET_ID_LOSSY_RANGE_START     192
> #define PACKET_ID_LOSSY_RANGE_LAST      255
> ```

Last valid lossy packet is actually 254. `PACKET_ID_LOSSY_RANGE_START` is the inclusive start of the range and `PACKET_ID_LOSSY_RANGE_SIZE` is the total number of lossy ids, including the starting one.

This should be changed to 254 and all the comparisons in `if`-statements need to be corrected, because it's not equivalent to `PACKET_ID_LOSSY_RANGE_START+PACKET_ID_LOSSY_RANGE_SIZE` which is the first invalid id after the lossy id block range, it's 1 less than that.
